						               													<description>Polak Ma&amp;#197;&amp;#130;y is a new memory based educational board game from Institute of Polish Remembrance. With help of puzzles, that you can also use for memory game, players can learn Polish national symbols such as Poland coat of arms, Polish flag and national anthem. Quick and fun way to teach children from age of four basics of national identity and heritage.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game features five mini games for example a quick game where three teams are racing to arrange a line of Polish anthem, the one which succeeded to do it first without a mistake wins - you check it by flipping cards if they are correct they will form Polish ensign. You can also play a game for two people by dividing puzzles by colours (red and white) once you have done it you lay them down in six rows (three white and three red). You start by playing memory game by finding cards from red and white rows with matching texts of Polish anthem, if a player succeed to do so he takes cards, player with most cards wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
